# Token Optimization — ITSM Ticket Intelligence Pipeline

## Problem Statement

A single PDF analysis consumes **~238K input tokens** across **4 sequential LLM calls**, each sending the **full raw PDF text** (~58K tokens per call). The token burn is:

| Call # | Purpose | Input | Output | Notes |
|--------|---------|-------|--------|-------|
| 1 | **User Extraction** | ~58K | ~0.5K | Extracts actor names → tiny JSON output |
| 2 | **Review/Timeline** | ~58K | ~2K | Full structured timeline extraction |
| 3 | **Service Manager** | ~58K | ~1.5K | SM insights from raw PDF |
| 4 | **Enterprise Architect** | ~58K | ~1K | EA technical analysis from raw PDF |
| **Total** | | **~233K** | **~5K** | **4× full PDF re-read** |

The raw PDF text is sent verbatim to all 4 calls. Calls 3 and 4 (SM + EA) are re-reading the entire raw document even though Call 2 already extracted a complete structured representation of the ticket.

