**Proposed**: 2 × ~58K + 2 × ~6K = **~128K input tokens** (**~45% reduction**)

### Phase 1 — Extraction (raw PDF required)

| Call | Input | What happens |
|------|-------|-------------|
| Call 1: User Extract | Raw PDF (~58K) | Extract actor names + suggested roles |
| Call 2: Review/Timeline | Raw PDF (~58K) + role mapping | Full structured JSON: incident metadata, timeline, communications, work notes, quality data |

### Phase 2 — Analysis (structured JSON only)

| Call | Input | What happens |
|------|-------|-------------|
| Call 3: SM Analysis | Structured JSON from Call 2 (~4-6K) + role mapping | Service Manager insights, sentiment analysis, improvement recommendations |
| Call 4: EA Analysis | Structured JSON from Call 2 (~4-6K) + role mapping | Technical root cause, tech stack, architectural gaps |

## Detailed Optimizations

### Optimization 1: Merge Call 1 into Call 2 (Optional — saves 1 full call)

> [!WARNING]
> This is the most impactful optimization but has a **UX trade-off**: the user currently sees the role-mapping wizard *before* the full analysis runs. Merging Call 1+2 would require either:
> - **(A)** Pre-extracting users with client-side regex (already partially implemented via `extractActorCandidatesFromText`) — **no LLM call needed**
> - **(B)** Keeping Call 1 separate but making it cheaper via text truncation (only send first ~2 pages for actor extraction)
>
> **Recommendation**: Option (B) — truncate input for Call 1 to first ~3000 tokens (the header/metadata section where actors are listed). This preserves the existing UX flow while cutting Call 1 input by ~95%.

### Optimization 2: Feed SM + EA from extracted JSON (Primary — saves ~116K tokens)

Instead of sending `pdfText` to Calls 3 and 4, send `JSON.stringify(reviewTranslations)` (the output of Call 2). This is the structured timeline + incident data the AI already extracted — it contains all the information SM and EA need.

**Changes required:**
- Modify the SM system prompt to clarify it's analyzing **pre-extracted structured data**, not raw PDF
- Modify the EA system prompt similarly
- Change `callLLM` invocation for SM and EA to pass the JSON string instead of `pdfText`

### Optimization 3: Client-side PDF text preprocessing (saves ~5-15K per call)

OmniTracker PDF exports contain significant boilerplate:
- Repeated page headers/footers
- Empty lines and whitespace
- Duplicated field labels across pages
- CSS/formatting artifacts from PDF extraction

**Add a `preprocessPdfText()` function** that:
1. Collapses multiple blank lines into single separators
2. Strips repeated header/footer patterns (page numbers, export timestamps)
3. Removes duplicate field labels that appear on every page
4. Trims excessive whitespace

Estimated savings: **5-15%** per raw PDF send.

### Optimization 4: Truncate Call 1 input (saves ~55K tokens)

The User Extraction call only needs the ticket header (actors, reporting person, affected person, history section headers). Send only the first ~3000 tokens + last ~1000 tokens of the PDF instead of the full text.

